casebody.data:
The State ex rel. Jerninghan, Appellant, v. Court of Common Pleas of Cuyahoga County et al., Appellees.

[Cite as State ex rel. Jerninghan v. Cuyahoga Cty. Court of Common Pleas (1996), 74 Ohio St.3d 278.]

(No. 95-1769 Submitted November 7, 1995 Decided January 10, 1996.) *279 Tommie Jeminghan, Jr., pro se. Per Curiam.

We affirm the judgment of the court of appeals. A writ of mandamus will not issue to compel an act already performed. State ex rel. Gantt v. Coleman (1983), 6 Ohio St.3d 5, 6 OBR 4, 450 N.E.2d 1163.

Judgment affirmed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, Wright, Resnick, F.E. Sweeney, Pfeifer and Cook, JJ., concur.
